name: PhoneNumber
title: Phone:
tooltip:
Why is my Phone number needed?
Insurance companies, their agents and partner companies may contact you to assist with your quoting process.

name: EmailAddress
title: Email:
mark: Never junk mail. We hate spam too.
tooltip:
Why is my Email needed?
Once your quote is completed, you may receive a copy of your quote. If you decide to purchase from a company, your email will be used to retrieve your quote for a quicker process.

name: ResidenceType
title: Homeowner?
tooltip: You can often get discounts if you combine your auto and homeowners insurance through the same insurer.

name: BirthDate
title: Date of birth:
tooltip: We need this information in order to compare quotes accurately. Additionally, drivers need to be at least 16 years of age to request a quote.

name: CreditRating
title: Credit Rating:
tooltip: In general, higher credit scores result in lower monthly auto insurance premiums, however rate formulas can vary per insurer. Comparing multiple quotes may help you save.

name: Occupation
title: Occupation:
tooltip: Please select the occupation category that best fits your current job description. Your occupation may qualify you for a discount; verification will be needed if you qualify.

name: Education
title: Education:
tooltip: Statistics show that someone with a higher education is less likely to be in an accident. If you or your spouse are applying for a single car insurance, you may save more by listing the one with higher level of education as the policy holder.

name: MaritalStatus
title: Marital Status:
tooltip: Statistics show that married drivers have fewer accidents than single drivers.

name: AnnualMiles
title: Annual Mileage:
tooltip: It is okay to estimate. You may round down or to the closest mileage, i.e. choose 2,500 if you drive less than 2,500 miles annually.

name: HadIncidents
title: Incidents in last 5 years?
tooltip: This includes traffic tickets, accidents, DUIs, License suspensions and insurance claims.

name: InsuredSince
title: Years Insured:
tooltip: It is okay to estimate. If you have only been insured for under a month, select 0.
